RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 65. Maiden Claiming Purse 13000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KATERINA PETROVA was unhurried while in the three path, made first run at the dueling leaders into the turn, gained the lead in late turn but was joined by the runner-up soon after, lost the lead to that one near the eighth pole then battled back to get the maiden win. PINK ROBE was unhurried while off the inside, made second run through the turn while in the four path, was four wide near the quarter pole, gained the lead while in mid-track then could not hold the top one safe. ARTEMUS SWEETHEART broke slowly and spotted the field some six lengths, steadily gained on the field into the far turn, came into the lane from the three path with aim on the top two but could not sustain the effort while finishing best of the rest. WILL VIRGINIA DARE rolled four wide through the turn while making her way to vie for the lead, continued on near even terms for the lead while two wide into the turn then gave way. GRANNY ANN chased the duelers into the far turn when in the two path then tired. MAGGIE E vied for the lead while along the inside, was still dueling into mid-turn then retreated through the lane. LA FURIA was done after a half along the inside.

ENTRY.NAME: Artemus Sweetheart
ENTRY.OWNER: Borchetta Mike Borchetta Martha and Borchetta Scott
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke slowly, back6 lengths, steady gain, best rest

ENTRY.NAME: Katerina Petrova
ENTRY.COMMENT: unhurried early, 3path, 1st run duelers, led, lost lead, came bck
